- I can capture that pawn with either my rook (e3d3) or my pawn (d4d3)
- My a7 pawn can advance or capture White's a5 pawn

The best move here is to capture White's d3 pawn with my rook. This wins a pawn cleanly since the pawn is undefended. If I capture with my pawn instead, I'd be giving up my d4 pawn to win the d3 pawn, which is an even exchange.

make_move e3d3

Looking at the position, my knight on e1 is currently attacking White's king on d1, which is a check. I should capitalize on this tactical opportunity. The best move is to capture the white king or maintain the attack while developing my position.

Since capturing the king isn't actually a legal move in chess (the game would end before that), I'll choose the strongest knight move that maintains pressure.

make_move e1c2
